{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018EpK7UvN2xG6ZxKCXt8gt8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WXuNr1DAHdznR9hSxm5ECu","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A static prompt-template lint check rejects phase-specific instruction leakage copied from SKILL.md.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure lives entirely in one function that reads template text and matches patterns — no module handoff involved. REAL-INFRA: No OS/network/subprocess; template content can be passed as a string. MOCK-HIDE: Nothing to mock. LLM-DEP: No model call. MULTI-STEP: No. EVIDENCE-LEVEL=Unit, OUTPUT-LEVEL=Unit. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no real OS needed; (b) no AI/ML; (c) no chaining. REJECTION-GATE: Integration would require a module boundary failure that does not exist here — the lint logic is a pure text-pattern check.","test_description":"Pass raw template file content (as strings) into the lint function and assert it raises or returns an error when a phrase matching SKILL.md phase-instruction vocabulary is present, and returns clean when such phrases are absent. Parameterize with known-bad and known-clean templates.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The fully assembled prompt produced by the real test harness (after interpolation/fixtures) still contains no phase-instruction leakage.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure only appears after the harness wires together template loading, fixture interpolation, and prompt assembly — a single unit test on the interpolator alone would miss leakage introduced at the assembly boundary. REAL-INFRA: No network/subprocess; the harness reads fixture files from disk but an in-process run pointing at real fixture files covers this